21. Rxd8 Rxd8 22. Rxd8 Kxd8 $15) 5... Bxd2+ 6. Qxd2 d6 (6... d5 7. e3) 7. Nc3
O-O 8. Qc2 (8. e4 e5 9. d5 (9. Be2 Bg4 $1 {[%csl Rd4]} 10. O-O (10. d5 a5 11.
b3 Na6 12. Qc2 (12. O-O Nc5 13. Qc2 a4 14. b4 Nb3 15. Rad1 Bxf3 16. Bxf3 Nd4
$15) 12... Nh5 13. g3 Bh3 14. Nd2 Nf6 $15) (10. h3 Bxf3 11. Bxf3 Nc6 (11... h6
12. Nd5 Qd8)) 10... Bxf3 11. Bxf3 Nc6 $15 {[%csl Rd4]}) (9. Bd3 {is a serious
mistake} Bg4 10. dxe5 dxe5 11. Be2 Bxf3 (11... Re8 $6 12. Nd5 {We achieve a
very instructive situation. Very often in Bogo-Indian, Nd5 is well met with
Qd8. Black doesn't want to change the structure.} Qd8 13. Qc2 Bxf3 14. Bxf3 Nc6
15. O-O Nd4 16. Qd3 c6 $19 {Black is strategically winning.}) 12. Bxf3 Nc6 {
[%csl Gd4][%cal Gc6d4]}) 9... a5 10. g3 a4 11. Qc2 Bd7 12. Bg2 Qe8 $1 {
remember this idea} 13. O-O Na6 14. Nd2 Nc5 15. f4 c6 {With a bishop on g2, we
