{Is the best move in this position} 9. O-O O-O 10. Qc3 h6 11. Re1 Be4) 9. b3 ({
The immediate} 9. d5 $6 {is not very good here} exd5 10. Nh4 Ne4 $1 $17 (10...
c5 $2 11. cxd5 $14)) 9... d6 10. O-O Nbd7 11. Bb2 Qb8 {Besides preparing the
advance b6-b5, Black also protects the bishop on b7} 12. Rfd1 (12. d5 {I
calculated that this advance is not giving an advantage for White} exd5 13. Nh4
dxc4 $11 {the computar found that White can force a draw after} 14. Nf5 Bxg2
15. Qg5 g6 16. Nh6+ Kg7 17. Nf5+ $11) 12... Be4 13. Rac1 c6 {My favourite plan
is to play c6 followed by b5 or d5} ({The engines show that Black could
immediately play} 13... b5 $1 14. c5 Nd5 (14... Bd5 $13) 15. Ne1 Bxg2 16. Nxg2
f5 $1 $11 (16... N7f6 $6 17. f3 $14)) 14. Bh3 b5 (14... h6 $1 {was the best
move in this position} 15. Nh4 d5 16. f3 Bh7 17. e3 c5 $1 {this move is good,
because White has permanent weaknesses on e3 and b3} 18. dxc5 bxc5 19. Bxf6
Nxf6 20. cxd5 exd5 21. Rxc5 Qxb3 {The isolated pawn is not important, because
White has a lot of weaknesses and weak king.}) (14... d5 $6 15. Ne5 Nxe5 16.
dxe5 Nd7 17. f3 Bg6 18. cxd5 cxd5 19. Qe3) 15. Nh4 $1 bxc4 16. bxc4 d5 17. f3
Bg6 18. Nxg6 $14 {White is slightly better, but I quicky took the initiative}
hxg6 19. e3 Nb6 20. Bf1 Nxc4 21. Bxc4 dxc4 22. Rxc4 Qb3 23. Rc3 Qb7 24. e4 Rfd8
25. Qc2 Ra6 26. Rcd3 Rb6 27. Bc3 Qa6 28. Be1 Rdb8 29. Qc3 Rb3 30. Qxb3 Rxb3 31.
Rxb3 g5 $1 {seeking for counterplay against the king} 32. h3 Kh7 (32... Qe2 $3
{i missed this move, which gives Black an advantage after:} 33. Rbd3 g4 $3 34.
hxg4 Nh7 35. Bf2 Ng5 36. Kg2 Nxf3 $19) 33. Rc1 Nh5 34. Bf2 f5 35. exf5 exf5 36.
Rbc3 Nf6 37. Rxc6 Qe2 38. Kg2 $2 g4 $2 (38... Nd5 $1 {This was my last chance
to win the game} 39. R6c5 Ne3+ 40. Kg1 Qxf3 41. Bxe3 Qxg3+ $1 $19 (41... Qxe3+
42. Kg2 Qe2+ 43. Kg1 f4 $17)) 39. hxg4 fxg4 40. R6c3 $11 {The position is
equal now and despite my efforts to win it, it ends in a draw after 20 moves.}
Nd5 41. Rh1+ Kg6 42. Re1 Qa2 43. Rc6+ Nf6 44. Re3 Kh7 45. Rc5 a4 46. Rf5 Kg6
