1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. c4 Bb4+ 4. Nbd2 b6 5. a3 Bxd2+ 6. Bxd2 Bb7 7. Bg5 h6 8.
Bh4 d6 9. e3 {normally White plays 9.e3, but 9.Nd2 is also possible} (9. Nd2 g5
10. Bg3 Nh5 11. e3 Nxg3 12. hxg3 Nd7 13. g4 Qe7 14. Rh2 O-O-O 15. Qc2 Nf6 16.
Be2 c5) {Now Black should take the bishop and castles long} 9... g5 10. Bg3 Ne4
11. Nd2 Nxg3 12. hxg3 Nd7 13. Rh2 (13. Nb1 Qe7 {keeping the structure flexible
and Black is perfectly fine. Black can choose between c5, d5, or h5 next} 14.
Nc3 O-O-O 15. Qc2 f5 16. O-O-O Nf6) 13... Qe7 14. Be2 (14. Qa4 {this is an
interesting possibility} a5 (14... c5 {or even} 15. dxc5 dxc5 {followed by
Kf8-g7})) 14... O-O-O 15. Bf3 d5 (15... f5 16. Bxb7+ Kxb7 17. Qf3+ Kb8 18.
O-O-O Nf6 {with a good game for Black}) 16. Qa4 (16. cxd5 exd5 17. g4 Nf6 $13)
16... Kb8 17. O-O-O f5 18. g4 Nf6 19. gxf5 exf5 20. cxd5 g4 21. Be2 g3 22. fxg3
Qxe3 23. Bf3 Nxd5 24. Rhh1 Qg5 25. Rhe1 Qxg3 26. Re5 Nf4 27. Qc4 Nd3+ 28. Kb1
Nxe5 29. dxe5 Bxf3 30. gxf3 Qxe5 {Rocki10 gibt auf (Lag: Av=0.38s, max=1.1s)} *

