) 13... g5 14. Bg3 Ne4 {Note that the advance ...e5-e4 works best only after
eliminating the opponent's dark-squared bishop.} 15. Qc2 Nxg3 16. hxg3 e4 17.
Nd2 f5 {This is the dream position Black was playing for. Later on, he managed
to convert his advantage.} 18. Kh2 Be6 19. Rh1 (19. Nb3 b6 20. Qc3 Rad8 21. a3
